<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Chicken Note</div>
<div class="nbunit" id="edn226">  226  Cf. 27.39 (35.01): &lsquo;They tell the story how one happy-go-gusty Ides-of-April morning ages and ages after the alleged misdemeanour when he MET a cad with a pipe.&rsquo; Encounter (generally hostile) is signalled in the <cite>Wake</cite> by the occurrence of the everyday phrase &lsquo;How do you do today, my good man,&rsquo; or some close variation. Here the phrase is given in Russian and Irish (<i>Zdravstvuyte gospodin?</i> and <i>Conas ta tu, a dhuine uasal?</i>, respectively).  </div>
